gui.witherstormmod.config.sickenedMobCon: Specifies if mobs should convert to sickened mobs once they die from wither sickness.
gui.witherstormmod.config.smartBossbar.d: The Wither Storm's bossbar and boss music will automatically toggle based on whether the player is underground or not. Disable to revert back to default bossbar/boss theme logic.
gui.witherstormmod.config.specialTargeti: Specifies if certain mobs (by default, players) should be targeted over others.

The percent chance certain mobs (by default, players) should be picked up over others.
Range: 0 ~ 100
gui.witherstormmod.config.squashHitbox.d: If true, the hitbox of the Wither Storm and Wither Storm Segment's will be shrunk vertically to one block. Enable if facing major server lag in the bigger Wither Storm phases
gui.witherstormmod.config.targetRunawayA:
Specifies the required time, in minutes, the Wither Storms ultimate target must be stationary in order to be able to count a runaway attempt when it tries to leave the stationary chunk radius.
Range: 1 ~ 20

Specifies if the Wither Storm should count the times its ultimate target leaves the stationary chunk radius. After a specified amount of attempts has been reached, the Wither Storm will accelerate to its Target Stationary Speed.

Specifies the amount of runaway attempts made by the Wither Storms ultimate target that must be met for it to begin a chase.
Range: 1 ~ 32
gui.witherstormmod.config.targetRunawayM:
Specifies the amount of time in minutes that the Wither Storm's ultimate target has begun to run away in order to slow back down again.
Range: 1 ~ 90
gui.witherstormmod.config.targetStationa:
If the player remains in a radius of chunks specified by this value for a specific amount of time, the Wither Storm will begin to move towards the player at a faster rate
Range: 0 ~ 16

Specifies the amount of time in minutes that the Wither Storm's ultimate target must be stationary in order for it to accelerate
Range: 1 ~ 120
gui.witherstormmod.config.targettingDist: Specifies when the Wither Storm is done chasing its ultimate target if it should become 'distracted' and go to a random nearby area.
gui.witherstormmod.config.tillShouldShow:
If the Wither Storm's ultimate target has a command block tool and the Wither Storm is at phase 7, a timer specified by this value (in minutes) + random will countdown until the hole will automatically appear.
Range: 1 ~ 30
gui.witherstormmod.config.tractorBeamBlo:
How far the tractor beams should search for distraction blocks, NOTE: High values may cause lag.
Range: 4 ~ 256
gui.witherstormmod.config.tractorBeamClu: Specifies if the Wither Storm should be able to pick up block clusters with its tractor beams.

Multiplies the speed of block clusters being pulled in by a Wither Storm's tractor beam by this value.
Range: 0.1 ~ 10.0
gui.witherstormmod.config.tractorBeamFlu:
Specifies the height of which tractor beams should remove water. The default of 63 is ocean height and upwards.
Range: -64 ~ 320
gui.witherstormmod.config.tractorBeamPar: Specifies if particles inside the tractor beams of the Wither Storm should render.
gui.witherstormmod.config.tractorBeamsRe: Makes it so the Wither Storm will remove fluids above Y 63 with its tractor beams.
gui.witherstormmod.config.tractorPullSpe:
Modifies the tractor beam pull speed, higher = faster.
Range: 0.1 ~ 1.0
gui.witherstormmod.config.ultimateTarget: Specifies the targeting type the Wither Storm should use to determine it's ultimate target.
gui.witherstormmod.config.usePhaseAsDist: Specifies if the Wither Storm should use the phase as a multiplier when calculating the time in ticks it takes for it to start accelerating, when its ultimate target is stationary.
gui.witherstormmod.config.vertexBufferRe: Specifies if CWSM should use more performant rendering when rendering Block Clusters and the Wither Storm's mass. NOTE: It is not recommended to disable this option unless necessary.
gui.witherstormmod.config.witherSickness: Specifies if mobs should be able to receive wither sickness
Specifies if an overlay should be applied to entities that renders wither sickness
gui.witherstormmod.config.witherStormInv: Specifies if the Wither Storm should regenerate its health and be melee attackable.
gui.witherstormmod.config.witherStormLOD: Specifies if the low res models should be used when being rendered via the distant renderer.
gui.witherstormmod.config.witherStormsFo: Specifies if smaller Wither Storms should follow one with more consumed entities.
gui.witherstormmod.config.witherStormSum:
Specifies the delay in minutes (+random) that the Wither Storm will be able to summon a Withered Symbiont.
Range: 1 ~ 20

withered_beacon.info:
The Withered Beacon will apply the selected effect to all nearby players in a very large radius.

In order to activate the Withered Beacon, a 3x3 square of lapis blocks must be constructed directly below it. Then, more layers of any valid beacon base blocks can be added in a pyramid shape to increase the strength of the selected effect.

Withered Support Beacons can be connected and will apply effects from an infinite distance in the direction the connecting beam makes. To connect a support beacon, make a 3x3 square directly underneath the beacon of either emerald, diamond, redstone, or iron blocks. Make sure the support beacon is within 5 blocks of the main beacon. There can only be one of each color and a maximum of four can be connected.
